1
00:00:50,551 --> 00:00:51,385
Hey.

2
00:00:52,678 --> 00:00:54,930
You're not treating Eui-ju like that
on purpose, are you?

3
00:00:55,723 --> 00:00:56,599
Like what?

4
00:00:57,308 --> 00:01:00,478
She told me she thinks
the essay and demerits are unfair.

5
00:01:01,187 --> 00:01:03,355
You're not doing that
because of the filming, right?

6
00:01:04,190 --> 00:01:05,024
Me?

7
00:01:05,775 --> 00:01:06,859
You wouldn't, right?

8
00:01:07,693 --> 00:01:09,653
I'm pretty sure that was all
just a misunderstanding.

9
00:01:13,449 --> 00:01:14,700
I know she didn't film us.

10
00:01:18,704 --> 00:01:19,789
Then why are you doing it?

11
00:01:20,664 --> 00:01:23,042
Why are you being so strict with just her?

12
00:01:25,586 --> 00:01:27,004
I can't accept her…

13
00:01:28,714 --> 00:01:31,050
only getting four points in math.

14
00:01:37,223 --> 00:01:38,057
Have some breakfast.

15
00:01:39,225 --> 00:01:41,852
I hear after-school classes don't happen
unless five kids sign up.

16
00:01:41,936 --> 00:01:42,853
I only have four.

17
00:01:43,938 --> 00:01:45,731
I heard yesterday, Woo-su already has ten.

18
00:01:52,488 --> 00:01:54,281
Oh, you found your glasses.

19
00:01:54,365 --> 00:01:55,866
Took you long enough to notice.

20
00:01:55,950 --> 00:01:56,951
Dude!

21
00:01:57,034 --> 00:01:58,619
What's going on? You found them.

22
00:01:59,703 --> 00:02:02,081
-Where did you find them?
-Did someone see your flyer?

23
00:02:02,873 --> 00:02:03,958
How much did you give them?

24
00:02:04,959 --> 00:02:05,918
Why would I give any?

25
00:02:06,585 --> 00:02:07,545
Look at this punk.

26
00:02:07,628 --> 00:02:09,129
The person didn't want a reward.

27
00:02:09,213 --> 00:02:10,256
-What?
-Why not?

28
00:02:11,382 --> 00:02:12,216
Who knows?

29
00:02:14,343 --> 00:02:15,678
What a lifesaver.

30
00:02:16,303 --> 00:02:17,680
You should bow to them, dude.

31
00:02:18,430 --> 00:02:21,600
You should express your gratitude
to bring more blessings back to yourself.

32
00:02:21,684 --> 00:02:23,602
Yeah, dude, it's the least you can do.

33
00:02:23,686 --> 00:02:26,188
-Otherwise you'll get pooped on again.
-Yeah, dude.

34
00:02:27,398 --> 00:02:29,066
CHAPTER 15:
BLINK TWICE IF YOU'RE HERE UNDER DURESS

35
00:02:29,149 --> 00:02:32,111
Is it just me or does your heart burst
every time Yoon picks up his pen?

36
00:02:32,194 --> 00:02:34,280
Even Si-on's breathing gets me
right in the feels.

37
00:02:34,363 --> 00:02:36,490
I wish I could be tied up
with that leather watch on Yoon's wrist.

38
00:02:36,574 --> 00:02:39,118
The way that Tae-ha looks at Yoon.
Is he for real?

39
00:02:50,254 --> 00:02:51,255
Hi.

40
00:02:51,338 --> 00:02:52,923
What's so funny?

41
00:02:53,007 --> 00:02:55,217
What? Well…

42
00:02:55,301 --> 00:02:56,760
The new thing I uploaded

43
00:02:57,386 --> 00:02:58,679
is causing quite a stir.

44
00:02:58,762 --> 00:03:00,598
Really? Show me.

45
00:03:01,307 --> 00:03:02,766
I can't, it's embarrassing. Sorry.

46
00:03:04,351 --> 00:03:06,437
The way you're being
so secretive about it…

47
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:09,607
Is it R-rated?

48
00:03:13,402 --> 00:03:15,279
No, don't be silly.

49
00:03:18,365 --> 00:03:21,493
It's not like BL, is it?

50
00:03:22,953 --> 00:03:24,204
BL?

51
00:03:24,288 --> 00:03:25,915
Yeah, you know,

52
00:03:25,998 --> 00:03:27,458
men liking other men.

53
00:03:29,668 --> 00:03:31,045
Oh, BL.

54
00:03:31,670 --> 00:03:33,297
I have heard of that.

55
00:03:35,507 --> 00:03:37,843
I don't get people
who like that kind of stuff.

56
00:03:40,387 --> 00:03:41,221
Of course.

57
00:03:42,264 --> 00:03:43,474
You're right.

58
00:03:44,099 --> 00:03:47,603
If it's a romance, why pair two guys
instead of a guy and a girl?

59
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:49,855
What's so fun about that?

60
00:03:51,649 --> 00:03:52,816
Right.

61
00:03:54,735 --> 00:03:55,653
Right.

62
00:03:57,529 --> 00:03:59,073
The weather's great, isn't it?

63
00:03:59,698 --> 00:04:00,532
Yeah.

64
00:04:01,450 --> 00:04:03,035
What's our first period?

65
00:04:09,291 --> 00:04:10,709
My dad always said…

66
00:04:12,920 --> 00:04:15,005
When faced with a difficult choice…

67
00:04:17,591 --> 00:04:18,717
Is that your application form?

68
00:04:19,510 --> 00:04:21,136
Finally got my fifth person.

69
00:04:21,220 --> 00:04:22,763
This is going to be an elite team.

70
00:04:23,347 --> 00:04:25,307
Let's do this,
rising star of the athletic world!

71
00:04:27,518 --> 00:04:28,769
Sorry, Mr. Jung.

72
00:04:34,108 --> 00:04:36,110
Taking the more difficult path…

73
00:04:36,986 --> 00:04:38,946
is the way to salvation.

74
00:04:42,074 --> 00:04:45,577
Mr. Jung, I really wanted to do
after-school PE.

75
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:48,122
But something came up.

76
00:04:48,205 --> 00:04:51,291
Blink twice if you're here under duress.

77
00:04:54,003 --> 00:04:55,462
She has a passion for math.

78
00:04:56,714 --> 00:04:59,049
She wants to get her score up
so I couldn't just say no.

79
00:05:00,634 --> 00:05:02,428
-Me?
-She should do what she's good at.

80
00:05:02,511 --> 00:05:04,596
Her long-distance running
is right up there.

81
00:05:05,097 --> 00:05:07,266
She obviously isn't an athletic type,
is she?

82
00:05:08,517 --> 00:05:10,227
Her face has got lazy written all over it.

83
00:05:11,061 --> 00:05:11,895
Me?

84
00:05:11,979 --> 00:05:12,855
No, it doesn't.

85
00:05:12,938 --> 00:05:14,356
I'm really hard-working.

86
00:05:14,440 --> 00:05:15,315
How much do you sleep?

87
00:05:17,901 --> 00:05:18,736
Ten hours.

88
00:05:21,196 --> 00:05:22,823
As long as you focus when you're awake.

89
00:05:23,741 --> 00:05:24,783
What rank are your grades?

90
00:05:27,870 --> 00:05:28,871
Ninth.

91
00:05:35,502 --> 00:05:37,087
Listen to your homeroom teacher.

92
00:05:39,590 --> 00:05:40,466
But, sir.

93
00:05:41,175 --> 00:05:43,510
They're not all nine.

94
00:05:56,315 --> 00:05:58,692
Today we're going to study the poem

95
00:05:58,776 --> 00:05:59,943
Invocation by Kim So-wol.

96
00:06:03,238 --> 00:06:05,783
INVOCATION

97
00:06:08,535 --> 00:06:10,621
KIM SO-WOL

98
00:06:14,708 --> 00:06:16,585
Let me read it aloud first.

99
00:06:17,252 --> 00:06:18,879
"A name which was shattered into pieces."

100
00:06:26,011 --> 00:06:28,180
Why doesn't Dong-ju
use the present I gave him?

101
00:06:30,390 --> 00:06:32,226
He probably doesn't want to burden you.

102
00:06:33,227 --> 00:06:36,355
If he uses it, you might feel obliged
to get him something else.

103
00:06:37,064 --> 00:06:37,940
Do you think?

104
00:06:41,443 --> 00:06:43,987
I'm going to tell him I like him
as soon as I turn 20.

105
00:06:45,823 --> 00:06:48,283
You really think
you'll still like him until then?

106
00:06:48,367 --> 00:06:50,828
You've never even lasted 200 days before.

107
00:06:50,911 --> 00:06:52,538
This time it's different.

108
00:06:54,623 --> 00:06:56,583
I'm really curious.

109
00:06:56,667 --> 00:06:58,836
Why do you like Mr. Yoon?

110
00:06:58,919 --> 00:07:00,087
Like what specifically?

111
00:07:00,170 --> 00:07:02,214
Not his looks.
There must be something special.

112
00:07:03,006 --> 00:07:04,675
Dong-ju

113
00:07:05,259 --> 00:07:06,093
is different.

114
00:07:08,095 --> 00:07:09,346
How is he different?

115
00:07:09,429 --> 00:07:11,515
Compared to all the other guys you dated.

116
00:07:20,149 --> 00:07:21,316
I feel sorry for him.

117
00:07:24,611 --> 00:07:25,445
What?

118
00:07:25,946 --> 00:07:27,197
I don't know.

119
00:07:27,281 --> 00:07:28,907
Just looking at his face

120
00:07:29,867 --> 00:07:30,742
makes me sad.

121
00:07:32,244 --> 00:07:33,871
It makes my heart ache.

122
00:07:39,376 --> 00:07:40,794
I guess.

123
00:07:40,878 --> 00:07:43,630
My mom said she married my dad
because she felt sorry for him.

124
00:07:43,714 --> 00:07:45,799
She also said never
to marry someone out of pity.

125
00:07:45,883 --> 00:07:48,218
That plenty of people
ruined their lives like that.

126
00:07:54,683 --> 00:07:56,852
But if you really like someone,

127
00:07:57,936 --> 00:07:59,605
I guess that's what it feels like.

128
00:08:00,189 --> 00:08:01,064
-Right?
-Yes.

129
00:08:04,193 --> 00:08:05,944
Feeling sorry for someone for no reason?

130
00:08:09,489 --> 00:08:11,617
I'm on cleaning duty again.

131
00:08:16,955 --> 00:08:18,916
-Good afternoon.
-Good afternoon.

132
00:08:20,584 --> 00:08:21,543
Great work today.

133
00:08:22,127 --> 00:08:24,379
Just look at that face.

134
00:08:24,463 --> 00:08:26,131
Who's ever going to feel sorry for him?

135
00:08:26,215 --> 00:08:28,258
Those on cleaning duty,
make sure you do it.

136
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:32,304
No one, whatsoever.
For the rest of his life!

137
00:08:32,971 --> 00:08:33,847
Dismissed.

138
00:08:34,556 --> 00:08:36,642
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

139
00:08:39,394 --> 00:08:42,356
I can't say I'm surprised,
but he's a real freak.

140
00:08:42,439 --> 00:08:43,982
He hits you with demerits on a whim.

141
00:08:44,566 --> 00:08:45,859
And now after-school math too.

142
00:08:45,943 --> 00:08:47,527
He's the devil.

143
00:08:48,862 --> 00:08:50,864
Let's do it together.

144
00:08:52,699 --> 00:08:55,160
I'd follow you to hell.

145
00:08:56,495 --> 00:08:57,704
But after-school math? No.

146
00:08:58,664 --> 00:09:01,208
Punishing someone
with what they hate most.

147
00:09:01,291 --> 00:09:02,918
Honestly, it's genius. Right?

148
00:09:04,461 --> 00:09:05,504
Hey, girls.

149
00:09:05,587 --> 00:09:06,463
Do you have plans?

150
00:09:06,546 --> 00:09:08,215
-Not really.
-Nope.

151
00:09:08,298 --> 00:09:09,216
Why?

152
00:09:09,299 --> 00:09:12,219
I have detention cleaning
and then after-school class.

153
00:09:12,302 --> 00:09:13,303
Why do you ask?

154
00:09:15,180 --> 00:09:17,724
There's something I want to do
now that I'm in Korea.

155
00:09:17,808 --> 00:09:19,393
-What?
-What is it?

156
00:09:19,476 --> 00:09:20,852
What is it?

157
00:09:22,229 --> 00:09:24,523
CHAPTER 16:
MATH IS ABOUT PERSEVERANCE

158
00:09:39,246 --> 00:09:40,247
Mr. Jung.

159
00:09:40,789 --> 00:09:44,501
I guess all I can do
is gaze on you from afar.

160
00:09:46,169 --> 00:09:48,213
Is this unbearable pain in my heart

161
00:09:48,297 --> 00:09:49,965
because of a love that can never be?

162
00:09:50,882 --> 00:09:54,094
Why is fate so cruel to us?

163
00:09:54,803 --> 00:09:56,847
What are you doing here?
Do you have something to tell me?

164
00:09:58,557 --> 00:10:00,225
Mr. Ga forced you, right?

165
00:10:01,643 --> 00:10:03,103
Gosh.

166
00:10:03,186 --> 00:10:04,021
No.

167
00:10:05,063 --> 00:10:06,982
Let me help you.

168
00:10:07,065 --> 00:10:08,233
Don't worry about it.

169
00:10:09,318 --> 00:10:10,235
There's no need.

170
00:10:12,237 --> 00:10:13,238
Oh, come on.

171
00:10:13,905 --> 00:10:14,990
I said it's fine.

172
00:10:15,073 --> 00:10:16,074
Thanks.

173
00:10:20,037 --> 00:10:21,621
I'm not saying this for the sake of it.

174
00:10:21,705 --> 00:10:22,998
You're really talented.

175
00:10:25,417 --> 00:10:26,793
So feel free to ask me anything.

176
00:10:27,669 --> 00:10:29,338
If you need anything, just tell me.

177
00:10:30,380 --> 00:10:31,214
Okay.

178
00:10:35,969 --> 00:10:36,803
So…

179
00:10:37,763 --> 00:10:41,099
You competed in the singles luge

180
00:10:41,183 --> 00:10:45,312
until you were forced to retire
after fracturing your left shin.

181
00:10:46,980 --> 00:10:48,190
How did you know that?

182
00:10:49,066 --> 00:10:50,359
I read a news article about it.

183
00:10:51,818 --> 00:10:53,362
It doesn't affect my daily life.

184
00:10:53,445 --> 00:10:57,324
But you were forced to retire after
finishing fourth at the Winter Games.

185
00:10:57,407 --> 00:10:59,034
You must have a lot of regrets.

186
00:11:00,494 --> 00:11:01,370
Are you asking

187
00:11:02,329 --> 00:11:03,789
if I regret not having won a medal?

188
00:11:09,044 --> 00:11:11,129
There's something
more important than that.

189
00:11:12,089 --> 00:11:14,758
As I watched the medalists
from below the podium,

190
00:11:15,258 --> 00:11:16,426
I realized something.

191
00:11:17,844 --> 00:11:21,223
Despite all the sweat I shed to compete
in the Games, they must have shed more.

192
00:11:23,475 --> 00:11:24,851
I thought I was going to die.

193
00:11:26,728 --> 00:11:28,355
They must have felt the same, right?

194
00:11:36,196 --> 00:11:38,156
In that moment,
my placing no longer mattered.

195
00:11:40,242 --> 00:11:41,451
And above all,

196
00:11:45,831 --> 00:11:47,416
I'd kept my promise to myself.

197
00:11:50,585 --> 00:11:51,795
I never gave up.

198
00:11:52,921 --> 00:11:53,839
That's what counts.

199
00:11:57,801 --> 00:11:59,302
If I'd done after-school PE,

200
00:11:59,386 --> 00:12:02,264
we could have talked all the time
and gotten close.

201
00:12:03,723 --> 00:12:05,225
If it wasn't for Mr. Ga…

202
00:12:13,567 --> 00:12:14,985
-Hello?
-Where are you?

203
00:12:17,195 --> 00:12:19,448
Come to my office
and get the printouts for the class.

204
00:12:21,199 --> 00:12:22,617
Can't you get someone else to do it?

205
00:12:22,701 --> 00:12:23,869
I'm sure Ha-su would love to.

206
00:12:23,952 --> 00:12:25,662
But you're the TA
for this after-school class.

207
00:12:25,745 --> 00:12:26,621
Since when?

208
00:12:26,705 --> 00:12:27,706
You've got three minutes.

209
00:12:31,585 --> 00:12:33,420
Mr. Jung, I need to go.

210
00:12:33,503 --> 00:12:34,921
-You're leaving?
-Yes.

211
00:12:35,005 --> 00:12:36,173
Goodbye.

212
00:12:43,680 --> 00:12:45,557
She's top of class one.

213
00:12:46,349 --> 00:12:48,518
And she's top of class three.

214
00:12:49,186 --> 00:12:51,480
This class is the best of the best.

215
00:12:52,105 --> 00:12:53,732
I don't belong here at all.

216
00:13:06,786 --> 00:13:08,205
Are you here to bring us these?

217
00:13:12,042 --> 00:13:14,544
No, I'm taking this class too.

218
00:13:14,628 --> 00:13:16,463
You? Why?

219
00:13:18,715 --> 00:13:20,091
Mr. Ga told me I should.

220
00:13:21,218 --> 00:13:22,093
Mr. Ga?

221
00:13:22,886 --> 00:13:24,971
It's probably so we don't waste our time.

222
00:13:25,555 --> 00:13:26,932
It's better she does all that.

223
00:13:28,433 --> 00:13:29,809
Do you think?

224
00:13:29,893 --> 00:13:30,769
I guess.

225
00:13:31,811 --> 00:13:33,897
She got four points
in the September mock exam.

226
00:13:36,525 --> 00:13:37,692
Four points?

227
00:14:28,660 --> 00:14:29,494
Where are you going?

228
00:14:30,078 --> 00:14:30,912
Mr. Ga.

229
00:14:31,538 --> 00:14:33,540
Can't you just let me go?

230
00:14:33,623 --> 00:14:36,918
I'm too bad at math to be in this class.

231
00:14:37,002 --> 00:14:40,255
My old tutor and my cousin both told me

232
00:14:40,338 --> 00:14:42,632
I don't have a head for math.
I think they were right.

233
00:14:42,716 --> 00:14:46,678
I'm totally hopeless with numbers.

234
00:14:47,262 --> 00:14:48,680
Unlike subjects you can memorize,

235
00:14:48,763 --> 00:14:51,308
more effort doesn't always mean
better scores.

236
00:14:53,143 --> 00:14:54,394
Those four points.

237
00:14:54,477 --> 00:14:56,146
How did you get them? Did you just guess?

238
00:14:57,022 --> 00:14:58,356
No, I solved them.

239
00:15:18,627 --> 00:15:19,628
There you go!

240
00:15:19,711 --> 00:15:21,880
When Gauss estimated the number of primes,

241
00:15:21,963 --> 00:15:25,091
he spent years manually calculating
every single prime up to three million.

242
00:15:25,175 --> 00:15:27,177
Math is about perseverance,
and you have it in spades.

243
00:15:27,260 --> 00:15:29,429
So get back in there.

244
00:15:29,512 --> 00:15:30,555
But…

245
00:15:31,473 --> 00:15:33,558
Since angle CFA

246
00:15:34,142 --> 00:15:36,394
is equal to angle CAF,

247
00:15:37,312 --> 00:15:41,149
AC equals CF, which is 14.

248
00:15:42,525 --> 00:15:43,652
Now try and solve it.

249
00:15:59,834 --> 00:16:02,712
What the heck?
Why is she putting lip tint on?

250
00:16:03,296 --> 00:16:04,673
And during class at that.

251
00:16:05,507 --> 00:16:06,466
No way!

252
00:16:08,259 --> 00:16:09,260
Wow!

253
00:16:09,969 --> 00:16:11,680
I know they say
birds of a feather and all.

254
00:16:11,763 --> 00:16:14,683
Does she like Mr. Ga? Amazing!

255
00:16:23,692 --> 00:16:25,568
When am I going to write episode three?

256
00:16:37,622 --> 00:16:38,832
Yeo Eui-ju!

257
00:16:38,915 --> 00:16:39,749
Yes, sir!

258
00:16:40,542 --> 00:16:41,501
Yes.

259
00:16:42,085 --> 00:16:43,586
Aren't you going to write episode three?

260
00:16:45,088 --> 00:16:46,715
Episode three?

261
00:16:47,215 --> 00:16:48,049
Yes.

262
00:16:48,675 --> 00:16:49,759
Explain how it goes.

263
00:16:58,393 --> 00:17:01,062
Readers will probably expect

264
00:17:01,146 --> 00:17:05,817
Yoon to pay back the ten million won
in episode three,

265
00:17:07,444 --> 00:17:10,363
but the highlight of episode three
is the swoon-inducing scene

266
00:17:10,447 --> 00:17:12,157
between Si-on and Yoon.

267
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:14,451
They're studying together
at Si-on's place,

268
00:17:15,034 --> 00:17:16,327
when Si-on says to Yoon,

269
00:17:17,454 --> 00:17:20,039
"You're really bad."

270
00:17:20,123 --> 00:17:22,459
"You keep making me think bad thoughts."

271
00:17:22,542 --> 00:17:23,543
Yoon replies,

272
00:17:24,127 --> 00:17:25,795
"Stop messing around."

273
00:17:25,879 --> 00:17:27,297
To which Si-on responds,

274
00:17:27,380 --> 00:17:29,716
"Do I look like I'm joking?"

275
00:17:29,799 --> 00:17:33,219
"I've never once joked with you!"

276
00:17:33,303 --> 00:17:35,263
…joked with you.

277
00:17:57,535 --> 00:18:00,580
Do the problems we covered in class today
and hand them in tomorrow.

278
00:18:01,414 --> 00:18:03,041
By tomorrow? How am I supposed…

279
00:18:07,504 --> 00:18:08,963
Damn it.

280
00:18:10,256 --> 00:18:14,719
CHAPTER 17:
JMT! (JUST A MARVELOUS TEACHER)

281
00:18:14,803 --> 00:18:17,055
There's something I want to do
now that I'm in Korea!

282
00:18:17,138 --> 00:18:19,265
GUESTHOUSE

283
00:18:19,349 --> 00:18:21,893
A pajama party!

284
00:18:28,650 --> 00:18:30,360
-Eui-ju!
-It's Eui-ju!

285
00:18:30,443 --> 00:18:31,569
Where have you been?

286
00:18:31,653 --> 00:18:33,238
Why are you so late?

287
00:18:33,321 --> 00:18:36,282
Is this the famous shaman's place?

288
00:18:36,366 --> 00:18:37,575
Be seated.

289
00:18:37,659 --> 00:18:39,244
How did you come to be here?

290
00:18:39,327 --> 00:18:41,204
-Is your name Yeo Eui-ju?
-Verily.

291
00:18:41,287 --> 00:18:42,288
Hello.

292
00:18:42,372 --> 00:18:43,832
-What took you so long?
-You're so late!

293
00:18:44,624 --> 00:18:46,626
Got you a present. Welcome!

294
00:18:46,709 --> 00:18:48,670
Oh, Eui-ju.

295
00:18:48,753 --> 00:18:49,754
So sweet!

296
00:18:49,838 --> 00:18:51,047
That's so cute!

297
00:18:51,130 --> 00:18:52,590
-Where's mine?
-It's really cute.

298
00:18:52,674 --> 00:18:54,592
-It's really cute.
-Thank you.

299
00:18:55,176 --> 00:18:56,553
Wow, you ate all this?

300
00:18:56,636 --> 00:18:57,929
-It's nothing.
-I'm bursting.

301
00:18:58,012 --> 00:18:59,722
Thus doth Kim Dan-ji proclaim.

302
00:18:59,806 --> 00:19:02,392
Eat like there's no tomorrow!

303
00:19:03,184 --> 00:19:04,269
I'm so full.

304
00:19:04,894 --> 00:19:06,104
What is that?

305
00:19:06,187 --> 00:19:07,689
Yeah! Now it's a party.

306
00:19:07,772 --> 00:19:08,982
-That's a must.
-Of course!

307
00:19:09,065 --> 00:19:11,317
Let me just make some space.

308
00:19:11,401 --> 00:19:13,528
-We always have a space for dessert!
-Rice cake sticks!

309
00:19:13,611 --> 00:19:14,529
Sweet potato.

310
00:19:14,612 --> 00:19:16,030
Let's go to the kitchen.

311
00:19:16,114 --> 00:19:16,990
Go to the kitchen!

312
00:19:17,073 --> 00:19:18,741
Let's go!

313
00:19:18,825 --> 00:19:20,827
Put this on before we go.

314
00:19:20,910 --> 00:19:21,744
This?

315
00:19:21,828 --> 00:19:24,414
Jenny, well done.

316
00:19:24,497 --> 00:19:26,457
Put them like this.

317
00:19:29,669 --> 00:19:30,879
And roast them.

318
00:19:32,338 --> 00:19:35,425
I'll show you the proper taste of Korea.

319
00:19:35,508 --> 00:19:37,510
I can't wait.

320
00:19:37,594 --> 00:19:39,679
Looks good, right?

321
00:19:39,762 --> 00:19:40,680
Yes.

322
00:19:41,848 --> 00:19:44,058
-It's really warm.
-It is, right?

323
00:19:46,769 --> 00:19:48,730
What? Do you need something?

324
00:19:49,856 --> 00:19:50,773
So…

325
00:19:53,109 --> 00:19:55,445
Hey, Jenny, by any chance,

326
00:19:57,155 --> 00:19:59,782
do you know A Night in Paris?

327
00:19:59,866 --> 00:20:01,117
A NIGHT IN PARIS

328
00:20:01,868 --> 00:20:03,995
You know that novel?

329
00:20:05,496 --> 00:20:08,207
Yeah, it used to be my favorite.

330
00:20:08,291 --> 00:20:13,171
The female protagonist, Isabelle,
meets her Brazilian boyfriend in Paris.

331
00:20:13,254 --> 00:20:14,964
At the Louvre.

332
00:20:15,048 --> 00:20:17,592
I did a double take
when I saw your messenger username.

333
00:20:17,675 --> 00:20:20,178
But what you told us about
how he asked you out was the same.

334
00:20:23,056 --> 00:20:25,475
So you knew all along.

335
00:20:25,558 --> 00:20:26,935
That I lied.

336
00:20:27,810 --> 00:20:29,479
Don't worry about it.

337
00:20:29,562 --> 00:20:31,731
Everyone wants to be the star
of their own novel.

338
00:20:31,814 --> 00:20:34,776
I just assumed you really like that novel.

339
00:20:36,110 --> 00:20:37,403
I don't really have a boyfriend.

340
00:20:37,987 --> 00:20:40,448
Everything I know about love
I learned from books.

341
00:20:42,158 --> 00:20:43,534
It's fine.

342
00:20:43,618 --> 00:20:44,994
It's no big deal.

343
00:20:45,578 --> 00:20:46,621
-Really?
-Yeah.

344
00:20:48,289 --> 00:20:50,166
I read it in translation first.

345
00:20:50,249 --> 00:20:52,794
And I really wanted to read the original.

346
00:20:52,877 --> 00:20:55,129
That's why I started learning Korean.

347
00:20:57,006 --> 00:21:00,468
You speak Korean this well
after learning from a novel?

348
00:21:01,678 --> 00:21:04,347
I read it so often
I practically memorized it.

349
00:21:07,016 --> 00:21:09,519
Do you like to read romance novels too?

350
00:21:09,602 --> 00:21:11,854
Well, you know.

351
00:21:12,480 --> 00:21:15,108
I started off by reading modern romances.

352
00:21:15,191 --> 00:21:18,820
Then I switched
to foreign romantic fantasy.

353
00:21:18,903 --> 00:21:20,196
And after that…

354
00:21:22,907 --> 00:21:23,992
And after that?

355
00:21:26,244 --> 00:21:27,787
Anyhow.

356
00:21:27,870 --> 00:21:30,707
Modern romance is the most mainstream.

357
00:21:32,750 --> 00:21:33,835
Right.

358
00:21:33,918 --> 00:21:37,630
I fell in love with Korea
after reading Korean romance web novels.

359
00:21:38,214 --> 00:21:40,299
Oh, I see.

360
00:21:41,175 --> 00:21:43,636
Which other novels did you enjoy?

361
00:21:45,847 --> 00:21:48,725
Fifty Shades of Mr. CEO.
Have you heard of it?

362
00:21:48,808 --> 00:21:50,643
-Of course! Have you read it?
-Yes!

363
00:21:51,310 --> 00:21:52,478
Did you read it too?

364
00:21:55,356 --> 00:21:56,232
-You did a great job.
-Looking good.

365
00:21:56,816 --> 00:21:58,943
-Hey, this rice cake is amazing.
-Stop it.

366
00:21:59,027 --> 00:22:00,278
You cooked these perfectly.

367
00:22:00,361 --> 00:22:02,155
Right? Have a bite.

368
00:22:02,780 --> 00:22:04,198
Oh, not yet.

369
00:22:04,282 --> 00:22:06,200
-Yeah, you need to add some kimchi.
-Sweet potatoes…

370
00:22:06,284 --> 00:22:08,619
-Kimchi?
-Yes, put it on top…

371
00:22:13,750 --> 00:22:15,126
How is it?

372
00:22:15,209 --> 00:22:16,794
-Wow!
-Isn't it great?

373
00:22:16,878 --> 00:22:17,962
Just marvelously tasty!

374
00:22:20,381 --> 00:22:21,966
You've got something on your face.

375
00:22:22,050 --> 00:22:24,177
-You've got something here as well.
-Come here.

376
00:22:24,260 --> 00:22:25,386
-Hey!
-No, I don't.

377
00:22:25,470 --> 00:22:27,055
Jenny, too.

378
00:22:27,138 --> 00:22:29,098
Hey!

379
00:22:30,266 --> 00:22:31,476
-With some grain syrup.
-Honey.

380
00:22:31,559 --> 00:22:33,102
-It's honey.
-Try it.

381
00:22:33,186 --> 00:22:34,103
It's good, right?

382
00:22:34,187 --> 00:22:35,480
-Do you like it?
-Isn't it great?

383
00:22:35,563 --> 00:22:37,565
This is just marvelously tasty too!

384
00:22:40,443 --> 00:22:41,903
This is nice.

385
00:22:41,986 --> 00:22:43,738
Man, I'm so full.

386
00:22:44,906 --> 00:22:46,699
Look at all those stars.

387
00:22:48,826 --> 00:22:51,579
There are so many of us, right?

388
00:22:52,955 --> 00:22:55,041
Like Mr. Ga said.

389
00:22:55,124 --> 00:22:57,168
We're all stars in the universe.

390
00:22:59,253 --> 00:23:02,799
When he says things like that,
doesn't he sound like the Little Prince?

391
00:23:03,508 --> 00:23:05,134
Know what I mean?

392
00:23:05,218 --> 00:23:08,221
Somewhere in the sky,
one of those shining stars belongs to me.

393
00:23:08,846 --> 00:23:10,890
And that star is speaking to me.

394
00:23:10,973 --> 00:23:12,225
Have you done your homework?

395
00:23:13,434 --> 00:23:15,394
-No!
-What is it?

396
00:23:18,147 --> 00:23:20,066
My math homework!

397
00:23:20,691 --> 00:23:22,652
No, my math homework.

398
00:23:22,735 --> 00:23:25,863
I couldn't even hang out properly
because of after-school math.

399
00:23:25,947 --> 00:23:27,406
When am I supposed to do my homework?

400
00:23:27,490 --> 00:23:29,075
I hate it.

401
00:23:29,158 --> 00:23:30,785
I hate it so much.

402
00:23:30,868 --> 00:23:33,121
Aren't you going to get more demerits
if you don't do it?

403
00:23:33,204 --> 00:23:35,540
-She's right.
-Whatever.

404
00:23:36,582 --> 00:23:37,750
What are you going to do?

405
00:23:37,834 --> 00:23:39,085
No idea.

406
00:23:39,168 --> 00:23:41,587
No idea, I don't care!

407
00:23:41,671 --> 00:23:44,841
Eui-ju, you've become gutsy.

408
00:23:44,924 --> 00:23:46,926
Did you see his face
when she faked being sick?

409
00:23:47,009 --> 00:23:48,553
-I remember.
-I know.

410
00:23:48,636 --> 00:23:50,304
He gave her a look of death.

411
00:23:50,763 --> 00:23:56,227
CHAPTER 18:
STRANGELY FAMILIAR, ALMOST MATHEMATICAL

412
00:24:05,027 --> 00:24:06,320
Mr. Ga.

413
00:24:07,947 --> 00:24:10,616
I couldn't do the homework.

414
00:24:11,159 --> 00:24:13,119
Can I just write out the solutions
ten times each?

415
00:24:13,202 --> 00:24:14,453
Did you even try?

416
00:24:17,540 --> 00:24:19,834
Keep trying until you can solve
at least one by yourself.

417
00:24:19,917 --> 00:24:21,586
Like you did on the mock exam.

418
00:24:22,712 --> 00:24:25,256
That only works sometimes.

419
00:24:25,339 --> 00:24:26,591
This isn't one of those times.

420
00:24:28,426 --> 00:24:29,260
Yeo Eui-ju.

421
00:24:30,720 --> 00:24:31,637
Yes, sir?

422
00:24:31,721 --> 00:24:33,514
What did I say math was on my first day?

423
00:24:40,188 --> 00:24:41,272
The universe.

424
00:24:44,358 --> 00:24:45,318
Euclid?

425
00:24:45,401 --> 00:24:46,819
In here, not during class.

426
00:24:56,370 --> 00:24:58,122
I said it's a subject
that requires thought.

427
00:25:00,124 --> 00:25:01,209
Yes, sir.

428
00:25:01,292 --> 00:25:03,794
You probably weren't paying attention.
Nor are you now.

429
00:25:08,049 --> 00:25:10,843
I thought solving one problem
would make you think.

430
00:25:12,887 --> 00:25:15,181
I didn't realize
you were such a lost cause.

431
00:25:18,476 --> 00:25:19,435
I'm very disappointed.

432
00:25:33,491 --> 00:25:34,784
I'm sorry.

433
00:25:48,130 --> 00:25:50,675
What on earth was he expecting of me
to be so disappointed?

434
00:25:52,677 --> 00:25:54,262
He even made me feel sorry for him.

435
00:25:58,641 --> 00:26:00,518
Still at least,
I got some dialogue out of it.

436
00:26:07,858 --> 00:26:10,361
So, how did he pay back the ten million?

437
00:26:10,444 --> 00:26:12,571
You keeping the rest
of this juicy story to yourself?

438
00:26:12,655 --> 00:26:13,823
Did she faint while writing?

439
00:26:13,906 --> 00:26:14,991
Give me my episode three!

440
00:26:15,074 --> 00:26:17,451
Episode three!

441
00:26:18,661 --> 00:26:20,705
The lines from Mr. Ga goes…

442
00:26:22,957 --> 00:26:24,667
I DIDN'T REALIZE YOU WERE SUCH…

443
00:26:26,294 --> 00:26:30,673
I'M VERY DISAPPOINTED, YOON

444
00:26:32,133 --> 00:26:34,385
I didn't realize
you were such a lost cause.

445
00:26:35,303 --> 00:26:37,096
I'm very disappointed, Yoon.

446
00:26:39,724 --> 00:26:40,725
Why?

447
00:26:45,438 --> 00:26:47,565
How can you read at a time like this?

448
00:26:51,068 --> 00:26:52,320
Stop messing around.

449
00:26:53,612 --> 00:26:55,740
Is Tae-ha gonna be waiting
outside your house again?

450
00:26:57,074 --> 00:26:58,159
YOON'S PAUSE INCENSES SI-ON

451
00:26:58,242 --> 00:26:59,201
I don't know.

452
00:27:00,202 --> 00:27:01,495
You're really bad.

453
00:27:04,665 --> 00:27:06,250
You keep making me think bad thoughts.

454
00:27:07,835 --> 00:27:10,546
I love it when you look at me, lying down.

455
00:27:10,629 --> 00:27:12,465
It makes me want to smush
my lips against yours.

456
00:27:12,548 --> 00:27:14,508
Until you can't breathe.

457
00:27:14,592 --> 00:27:16,510
SI-ON PRESSED AGAINST YOON,
HIS BREATHING RAGGED

458
00:27:29,190 --> 00:27:31,776
Now that's a proper cliffhanger.

459
00:27:31,859 --> 00:27:34,445
There's no way
you can skip the next episode.

460
00:27:49,126 --> 00:27:50,836
That smell

461
00:27:50,920 --> 00:27:53,798
isn't one I'm used to in the library.

462
00:27:56,133 --> 00:27:58,636
And yet, it's strangely familiar.
How should I put it…

463
00:27:58,719 --> 00:28:02,223
Like a skincare lotion
that a jerk would use.

464
00:28:03,057 --> 00:28:05,184
Almost…

465
00:28:06,435 --> 00:28:08,646
mathematical?

466
00:28:15,861 --> 00:28:17,530
I must be mistaken.

467
00:28:17,613 --> 00:28:19,824
Keep calm, Eui-ju.

468
00:28:21,409 --> 00:28:23,160
It's probably nothing.

469
00:28:24,286 --> 00:28:27,790
No, it's nothing.

470
00:28:47,143 --> 00:28:48,060
Move!

471
00:28:48,686 --> 00:28:49,895
Stay right there, Yeo Eui-ju!

472
00:28:51,564 --> 00:28:52,523
I mean,

473
00:28:55,025 --> 00:28:55,860
I.

474
00:28:57,236 --> 00:28:58,070
Muk.

475
00:30:15,814 --> 00:30:17,816
Subtitle: Paul Carver

